{{- /*  Trojans and viruses  */}}
<div class="modal fade" id="tavModal" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="tavModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg modal-dialog-centered modal-dialog-scrollable">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h1 class="modal-title fs-5" id="tavModalLabel">Trojans and software viruses</h1>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <p class="fs-5 fw-semibold lead text-info-emphasis">We never intentionally distribute viruses, trojans or any form of malware.</p>
        <p>
          Unfortunately, current virus tools employ a scan and detection technique known as heuristic scanning. 
          In addition to the standard scanning for malware code using a denylist, heuristic scanning looks at the program for malware-like behavior. 
          Many scene intros and cracktros implement self-decrypting and decompressing techniques, which, unfortunately, is also standard behavior for malware.
        </p>
        <p>
          Scanning for behavior in software is never 100% accurate, and an over-sensitive heuristic scan can report what are known as false positives. 
          A scan that has incorrectly claimed a potential threat but cannot pinpoint what that threat is and instead gives it a generic name.
        </p>
        <p>
          Some files offered on Defacto2 do get flagged as a possible virus or trojan threat, but we do not believe they are dangerous.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-footer">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
